WEBVTT

00:01.802 --> 00:03.871 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But, first, in
the German city
of Cologne, more than 100 women
have filed

00:03.904 --> 00:09.376 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
complaints about being sexually
molested by
men described as being of --
quote -- "North

00:09.409 --> 00:11.578 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
African or Arab origin."

00:11.612 --> 00:16.550 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The attacks have polarized
public opinion
in Germany over its open door
policy, which

00:16.583 --> 00:21.555 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
has seen it take in more than a
million asylum
seekers amid the refugee crisis.

00:21.588 --> 00:25.792 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
From Cologne, special
correspondent Malcolm
Brabant reports.

00:25.826 --> 00:33.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Dominated by
its magnificent
cathedral, Cologne has a
reputation for great

00:33.233 --> 00:38.205 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
tolerance. But the city's
open-mindedness
has been stretched to the limit
by what happened

00:38.238 --> 00:43.243 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
beneath the spires and near the
railway station
as the new year fireworks were
let off in

00:43.277 --> 00:47.281 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
an aggressive manner by some of
those in the
crowd.

00:47.314 --> 00:59.026 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It took several days for the
full extent of
the criminal activity to be
revealed. This

00:59.059 --> 01:04.498 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
young woman, who asked to remain
anonymous,
was one of more than 100 who
were assaulted.

01:04.531 --> 01:09.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator): All
of a sudden,
these men around us began
groping us. They

01:09.169 --> 01:13.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
touched our behinds and grabbed
between our
legs. They touched us
everywhere. So, my girlfriend

01:13.974 --> 01:18.011 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
wanted to get out of the crowd.
When I turned
around, one guy grabbed my bag
and ripped

01:18.045 --> 01:22.082 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it off my body. I thought to
myself that,
if we stay here in this crowd,
they could

01:22.115 --> 01:25.185 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
kill us, they could rape us, and
nobody would
notice.

01:25.218 --> 01:29.323 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I thought we simply had to
accept it. There
was no one around us who helped
or was in

01:29.356 --> 01:35.595 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a position to help. All I wanted
was to get
out. I was scared that I
wouldn't leave this

01:35.629 --> 01:39.132 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
crowd alive. I was scared that
if someone
showed up with a knife, I could
be raped in

01:39.166 --> 01:42.002 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the middle of the street.

01:42.035 --> 01:46.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have nightmares at night and I
can't sleep
anymore. I am too scared to go
outside on

01:46.173 --> 01:49.309 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
my own. And, of course, I'm now
scared to
go to big cities.

01:49.343 --> 01:54.681 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Writer Alice
Schwarzer is
regarded as one of Germany's
leading women's

01:54.715 --> 01:59.553 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
rights activists. She believes
what happened
in Cologne marks a line in the
sand in the

01:59.586 --> 02:01.455 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
debate over immigration.

02:01.488 --> 02:05.125 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALICE SCHWARZER, Women's Rights
Activist (through
translator): In the last 40
years, we have

02:05.158 --> 02:09.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
very successfully fought for our
rights as
women, for our freedom, for our
access to

02:09.296 --> 02:13.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the world, and that we are free
to move around
in it. And it's going to stay
that way, of

02:13.533 --> 02:15.435 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
course.

02:15.469 --> 02:18.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If someone has to change, then
it's the men
who come from cultures where
women are traditionally

02:18.271 --> 02:23.010 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
robbed of their rights, where
they are repressed
and the victims of violence.
These men have

02:23.043 --> 02:27.014 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
been brutalized by the violence
and trauma
of war. They have problems, and
I don't want

02:27.047 --> 02:31.518 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
